                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/10190: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cole</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-22T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 22, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 22—2:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>158. Your 91, April 18.<note n="24" xml:id="d249fn24">See footnote 19, <ref
                            target="#pg_292">p. 292</ref>.</note> Message conveyed as instructed.
                        Chatel’s<note n="24a" xml:id="d249fn24a">Yves Chatel, Secretary General of
                        the Delegation General in French Africa.</note> reaction: Warning
                    strengthens Marshal’s hands as well as Weygand’s. Vichy informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
